name: Assertion Effectiveness
query:
select 
da0.a0 as '0 Assertion Test Cases',
da1.a1 as '1 Assertion Test Cases',
da2.a2 as '2 Assertions Test Cases',
da3.a3 as '3 Assertions Test Cases',
da4.a4 as '4 Assertions Test Cases',
da5.a5 as '>= 5 Assertions Test Cases',
(da0.a0+da1.a1+da2.a2+da3.a3+da4.a4+da5.a5) as 'Total Test Cases'

from (select count(*) as 'a1' from (select count(tc.name) from `tabTest Case` tc left join `tabAssertion` a on a.parent=tc.name group by a.parent having count(a.name)=1) as dc) da1
join
(select count(*) as 'a2' from (select count(tc.name) from `tabTest Case` tc left join `tabAssertion` a on a.parent=tc.name group by a.parent having count(a.name)=2) as dc) da2
join
(select count(*) as 'a3' from (select count(tc.name) from `tabTest Case` tc left join `tabAssertion` a on a.parent=tc.name group by a.parent having count(a.name)=3) as dc) da3
join
(select count(*) as 'a4' from (select count(tc.name) from `tabTest Case` tc left join `tabAssertion` a on a.parent=tc.name group by a.parent having count(a.name)=4) as dc) da4
join
(select count(*) as 'a5' from (select count(tc.name) from `tabTest Case` tc left join `tabAssertion` a on a.parent=tc.name group by a.parent having count(a.name)>=5) as dc) da5
join
(select count(*) as 'a0' from (select count(tc.name) from `tabTest Case` tc left join `tabAssertion` a on a.parent=tc.name where a.name is null group by tc.name ) as dc) da0
